Robbie Rogers became America's first openly gay athlete in professional team sport last night when he played a soccer match for Los Angeles Galaxy.

Rogers made his ground-breaking debut last night as a  77th minute substitute with his side leading the Seattle Sounders 4-0.

The 25-year-old received loud cheers from the crowd as he ran onto the pitch and fans chanted his last name.

