Rogers had retired from the sport after 
announcing he is gay but returned to end his hiatus from the game with British star David Beckham's former team.

In April he talked about hiding his sexuality in the 
'macho' world of professional sports.

In a TV interview with ABC's
Nightline, Rogers spoke about going to visit his tight-knit, 
conservative, Catholic family for the first time since coming out in 
February.

Rogers said he hid his homosexuality so he could fit in with the soccer environment.

'Because
it's sports. It's the stereotype that you're supposed to be this manly 
guy that is making tackles. It's beating up on other guys,' Rogers 
explained.

Rogers rose to prominence at
Columbus Crew in MLS, scoring 13 goals in over 100 appearances and 
earning international colors in the process.

